edu.harvard.integer.common.selection

Class Filter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.harvard.integer.common.BaseEntity
      • edu.harvard.integer.common.selection.Filter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDInterface, java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public class Filter
extends BaseEntity
    A filter is the way users tell the system the range of ServiceElements they want to select for some purpose.

    Note that the selections attributes (e.g., technology, provider, etc.) are AND. For example if the technology is routing AND a provider is acme service company, then only service elements from the acme service company will be the output of the filter. If one of the attributes like location or service is null, then it is as if the user had selected all possibilities to which they have access.
